src/lib/components/DashDatetimepicker.re.description:
Dash Datetime Range Picker is a component for selecting two dates (including times).
It takes `startDate` and `endDate` as main properties and renders two inputs
which open datepickers when they are clicked.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.

endDate.description: The endDate of the range picker. It will fire a dash callback if it is updated.

startDate.description: The startDate of the range picker. It will fire a dash callback if it is updated.

utc.description: When true, input time values will be interpreted as UTC (Zulu time) by Moment.js. Otherwise they will default to the user's local timezone.
